1. IoT Hardware (Sensors & Equipment)IoT devices collect continuous, real-time data from the gym floor and the user's body.Connected Machines: Smart treadmills, stationary bikes, and resistance machines that automatically adjust speed, incline, and weight based on the user's profile.Wearables & Biometric Sensors: Smartwatches, heart rate monitors, and smart rings that track real-time heart rate, blood oxygen, sleep, and recovery readiness.Smart Gym Access & Tracking: RFID or QR-code enabled access points that track individual attendance and equipment usage

